HEADWORD: Hyperdulia
<hw>Hy`per*du*li"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>hyper-</ets> + <ets>dulia</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>hyperdulie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>Veneration or
worship given to the Virgin Mary as the most exalted of mere creatures;
higher veneration than dulia.</def> <rj><au>Addis &
Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
